  "prompt": "Is there a way to tell if someone in Skype is currently in a call or messaging someone?",
  "response": "In Skype, you can see the user's current status, which can indicate if they're available, busy, or in a call:\n\n1. Look for status indicators next to their name:\n- Green circle: Available\n- Red circle: Busy or in a call\n- Yellow/Orange circle: Away\n- Gray circle: Offline\n\n2. Some status messages might also explicitly say \"In a call\" or \"Busy\"\n\n3. If someone is actively in a call, you might see a phone icon next to their name\n\nKeep in mind that users can manually set their status, so it's not always 100% accurate.",
